<div class="official-rules">
    <p align="center"><strong>Race To DeLeon Weekly Challenge</strong><strong> </strong><br />
        <strong>Official Rules</strong></p>
    <p><strong>NO PURCHASE OR PAYMENT NECESSARY. A PURCHASE WILL NOT IMPROVE YOUR CHANCE OF WINNING.&nbsp; VOID IN QUEBEC, GUAM, PUERTO RICO, THE U.S. VIRGIN ISLANDS AND OTHER U.S. TERRITORIES AND POSSESSIONS AND WHERE PROHIBITED BY LAW. THIS PROMOTION IS IN NO WAY SPONSORED, ENDORSED, ADMINISTERED BY, OR ASSOCIATED WITH FACEBOOK, &nbsp;TWITTER, INSTAGRAM AND/OR TUMBLR.&nbsp; </strong></p>
    <p><strong>BY ENTERING THIS PROMOTION, ENTRANT AGREES TO THESE OFFICIAL RULES.</strong></p>
    <p><strong><u>Eligibility</u></strong><br />
        The Race To DeLeon Weekly Challenge (the &quot;Challenge&quot;) is open only to legal residents of the fifty (50) United States (including the District of Columbia) and Canada (excluding Quebec), who are thirteen (13) years or older at the time of entry. &nbsp;Void in Quebec, Guam, Puerto Rico, the U.S. Virgin Islands and other U.S. territories and possessions and where prohibited by law. No purchase necessary to enter the Challenge. &nbsp;Employees of ABC, Inc. d/b/a Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures, 500 South Buena Vista Street, Burbank, CA 90051 (the &quot;Sponsor&quot;), Brandmovers, Inc., 1575 Northside Drive, Building 200, Atlanta, GA 30318 (&quot;Administrator&quot;), Ford Motor Company, Royal Purple, LLC, MagnaFlow, or any of their respective affiliates, subsidiaries, licensors, advertising agencies, or any other company or individual involved with the design, production, execution or distribution of the motion picture titled &ldquo;Need For Speed&rdquo; and/or the Challenge (collectively with Sponsor and Administrator, the &quot;Challenge Entities&quot;) and their immediate family (i.e. spouse, parents and step-parents, grandparent and step-granparents, siblings and step- siblings, and children and step-children) and household members of each such employee are not eligible to enter or win. &nbsp;The Challenge is subject to all applicable federal, state, municipal, provincial and local laws and regulations. &nbsp;Participation constitutes entrant's full and unconditional agreement to these Official Rules (the &ldquo;Rules&rdquo;) and Sponsor's decisions, which are final and binding in all matters related to the Challenge. &nbsp;Winning a prize is contingent upon fulfilling all requirements set forth herein.</p>
    <p><strong><u>Challenge Periods</u></strong><br />
        The Challenge begins on January 31, 2014 at 9:00:00 AM Pacific Time (&quot;PST&quot;) and ends on March 16, 2014 at 11:59:59PM PST (the &quot;Challenge Period&quot;). &nbsp;&nbsp;The Challenge Period consists of six (6) separate and distinct Challenges (each a &ldquo;Weekly Challenge&rdquo; and collectively referred to as &ldquo;Weekly Challenges&rdquo;).&nbsp; The exact entry period for each Weekly Challenge (each a &ldquo;Weekly Entry Period&rdquo;) is provided in the chart below (the &ldquo;Entry Chart&rdquo;).&nbsp; &nbsp;The Website (defined below) clock is the official timekeeper for these Challenges.</p>
    <p><strong><u>How to Enter</u></strong><br />
        <a name="id.665f82c5954c" id="id.665f82c5954c"></a>During the Challenge Periods, there are two possible ways to enter: </p>
    <ul>
        <li>If an entrant (&quot;Entrants&quot;) is a first time visitor to www.RaceToDeLeon.com (&ldquo;Website&rdquo;) then the Entrant will fill out the official entry form located on the Website with all required information (collectively, &ldquo;Entry Form&rdquo;).&nbsp; Entrant must agree to the Race to DeLeon Weekly Challenge Official Rules and Terms of Use, then connect to Facebook and accept Facebook permissions to submit the Entry Form (the &ldquo;Basic Entry&rdquo;).&nbsp; <strong>Entrant will only need one (1) Basic Entry to be able to participate in any of the Weekly Challenges.</strong> Upon completion, Entrant will then be eligible to choose their avatar car to participate in the Weekly Challenges during the Challenge Period (collectively, &ldquo;Registration&rdquo;). All Registrations must be submitted by 11:59:59 p.m. PST on the applicable End Date listed in the Entry Chart (below) to be eligible to participate in the applicable Weekly Challenge.&nbsp; Entrant must accept Facebook permissions to participate and must be a registered member of Facebook with an account in good standing.&nbsp; &nbsp;To become a registered member of Facebook (registration is free), go to <a href="http://www.facebook.com">www.facebook.com</a> and follow the instructions to become a registered member and create an account (&ldquo;<strong>Account</strong>&rdquo;).&nbsp; <strong>By accepting Facebook permissions, the Race To DeLeon application (1) will have access to your public profile information, including your profile photograph; and (2) WILL ALLOW SPONSOR AND ITS AFFILIATES TO SEND YOU FACEBOOK NOTIFICATIONS PERTAINING TO THE RACE TO DELEON PROMOTION</strong><strong>.<br />
            </strong></li>
        <li>If an Entrant has visited the Website before and previously filled out the Entry Form then the Entrant will need to accept the Race to DeLeon Weekly Challenge Official Rules and Terms of Use. Upon completion, Entrant will then be eligible to choose their avatar car to participate in the applicable Weekly Challenge during the Challenge Period. All Registrations must be submitted by 11:59:59 p.m. PST on the applicable End Date in the Entry Chart below to be eligible to participate in the applicable Weekly Challenge. &nbsp;</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Basic Entry may hereafter be referred to as &ldquo;Entry&rdquo; or &ldquo;Entries&rdquo;.&nbsp; Regardless of whether a person has more than one (1) email address or more than one (1) person use the same email address, Basic Entries are limited to one (1) per person/email address during the Challenge Period. </strong></p>
    <p>Any attempt by any participant to enter by using multiple/different email addresses, identities, registrations and logins, or any other methods will void that participant's entries and that participant may be disqualified, at the sole discretion of Sponsor. &nbsp;Use of any automated system to participate is prohibited and may result in disqualification. Sponsor is not responsible for lost, late, incomplete, invalid, unintelligible or misdirected entries, which may be disqualified. &nbsp;In the event of a dispute regarding who submitted a Registration or Entry, the Registration or Entry will be deemed submitted by the authorized account holder of the e-mail address connected with the Entry Form, from which the Entry was submitted. &nbsp;&quot;Authorized account holder&quot; is defined as the natural person who is assigned to an e-mail address by Internet access provider, online service provider, or other organization (e.g., business, educational institution, etc.) that is responsible for assigning e-mail addresses for the domain associated with the submitted e-mail address. &nbsp;No automatically generated entries will be accepted.</p>
    <p><strong><u>Privacy Policies and Data Collections</u></strong><br />
        Information provided by you for the Challenge on the Entry Form is subject to Sponsor&rsquo;s privacy policy located at <a href="http://www.realjohncarter.com/home/%3Ehttp:/corporate.disney.go.com/corporate/pp.html">http://corporate.disney.go.com/corporate/pp.html</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp; By entering the Challenge, each Entrant agrees that the Sponsor and/or Administrator has the right to contact the Entrant by (1) email accounts provided on the Entry Form to administer and fulfill theChallenge; AND (2) Facebook notifications to administer Entrant&rsquo;s participation in the Race To DeLeon Promotions. <br />
        <strong>The Challenge is in no way sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with Facebook, Tumblr Instagram or Twitter. &nbsp; Facebook, Tumblr, Instagram and Twitter are registered trademarks. &nbsp;Such use is not intended to suggest or imply the sponsorship, endorsement, or the approval of the Challenge by Facebook, Tumblr, Instagram or Twitter.</strong></p>
    <p><strong><u>Weekly Challenges</u></strong><br />
        Each week throughout the Challenge Period, there will be a Weekly Challenge.&nbsp; Entrants may participate in the Weekly Challenges by participating in the posted activities (each a &ldquo;Task&rdquo; and collectively the &ldquo;Tasks&rdquo;) during the applicable Weekly EntryPeriod.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Once an Entrant has completed a particular Task, that Entrant will be awarded a set number of points. &nbsp;The number of points associated with each Task can be found in the Entry Chart under &ldquo;Points.&rdquo;&nbsp; In addition, if an Entrant participated in Sponsor&rsquo;s &ldquo;Pre-Qualifying Race to DeLeon Sweepstakes,&rdquo; which began on December 20, 2013 and ended January 6, 2014 (&ldquo;Phase 1&rdquo;), they may have accumulated points in Phase 1 which will be used only towards their avatar car selection when they first register for the Challenge. &nbsp;The points gained in Phase 1 that are applicable to the avatar car selection are as follows: (i) thirty (30) points for sharing the trailer on Twitter or Tumblr (up to a maximum of sixty (60) points); and (ii) three hundred (300) points for each friend that Entrant recruited to participate in Phase 1.&nbsp; Each Entrant&rsquo;s points will reset to zero at the beginning of each Weekly Challenge and points will not carry over into the subsequent Weekly Challenge. &nbsp;Any points accumulated in Phase 1 will have no bearing on determining potential winners and will only be applied to the selection of the Entrants avatar car when they first register for the Challenges.</p>
