    <p><strong><u>Leaderboard </u></strong><br />
        An Entrant&rsquo;s point accumulation can be viewed on the Entrant&rsquo;s dashboard on the Website (the &ldquo;Dashboard&rdquo;).&nbsp; In addition, participants can view the Entrants with the most points for the current Weekly Challenge on the leaderboard (the &ldquo;Leaderboard&rdquo;) on the Website.&nbsp; Please note that points may not appear on the Entrant&rsquo;s Dashboard or Leaderboard immediately and could take up to seventy-two (72) hours to appear therefore the Leaderboard and/or Dashboard may not be accurate at any given time.&nbsp; </p>
    <p><strong><u>Winner Determination</u></strong><br />
        There will be a total of thirty-three (33) Weekly Challenge Winners (the &ldquo;Weekly Challenge Winners&rdquo; and each a &ldquo;Weekly Challenge Winner&rdquo;) in the Challenge.&nbsp; The number of Weekly Challenge Winners per Weekly Challenge are indicated in the Weekly Prizes section below. The Weekly Challenge Winners will be determined by those Entrants with the greatest number of total points for the applicable Weekly Challenge Period.&nbsp; If there is more than one prize for the applicable Weekly Challenge, the Entrant with the most points will be determined the potential grand prize winner, the Entrant with the second most points will be determined the first prize winner, and so on.&nbsp; Such determination will be made by Administrator in its sole discretion using the Administrator&rsquo;s computer systems and in no event will the Leaderboard or Dashboard be determinative of the Weekly Challenge Winners.&nbsp; </p>
    <p>The potential winners will be contacted via his/her email address as provided on the Entry Form on or about Approximate Winner Determination Date as displayed in the Entry Chart above (&ldquo;Determination Date&rdquo;), and may be awarded a Prize (subject to verification of eligibility and compliance with the terms of these rules). Sponsor's decisions as to the administration and operation of the Weekly Challenges and the determination of potential winners is final and binding in all matters related to the Weekly Challenges. In the event of a tie, the Entrant that obtained the highest level of points within the shortest time period as determined by the Website clock, will be determined to be the potential winner. Administrator will send a notification message (&quot;Message&quot;) to the potential winner's email account on or about the same day of the Determination Date.</p>
    <p>Failure to respond to the Message within two (2) days of notification, or return of message notification as undeliverable after two (2) attempts will result in disqualification and an alternate potential Winner may be selected, time permitting. &nbsp;The prize will be awarded, provided it is validly claimed by April 30, 2014, after which no alternate winner will be selected, nor unclaimed prize awarded. </p>
    <p>THE POTENTIAL WINNERS ARE SUBJECT TO VERIFICATION BY ADMINISTRATOR AND SPONSOR&rsquo;S DECISIONS ARE FINAL AND BINDING IN ALL MATTERS RELATED TO THE CHALLENGE.</p>
    <p><strong><u>Verification of Potential Winners</u></strong><br />
        In order to be confirmed as a Weekly Challenge Winner, and without limitation of any other terms herein, the potential Weekly Challenge Winner (or potential Weekly Challenge Winner&rsquo;s parent/legal guardian if potential Weekly Challenge Winner is deemed a minor in the state/province of his/her residence) must provide satisfactory proof, as determined by Sponsor in its sole discretion, that such potential Weekly Challenge Winner is an eligible Entrant, including but not limited to providing a copy of the potential Weekly Challenge Winner&rsquo;s government-issued identification and/or additional information required by Sponsor in order to verify eligibility and compliance with these Official Rules. All potential winners from Canada will be required to correctly answer a time-limited skill testing question without any assistance in order to be eligible to receive a prize or such prize will be forfeited.&nbsp; Potential Weekly Challenge Winner (or potential Weekly Challenge Winner&rsquo;s parent/legal guardian if potential Weekly Challenge Winner is deemed a minor in the state/province of his/her residence) will be required to sign and return to Administrator, within three (3) days of the date notice is sent, an affidavit of eligibility, and a liability/publicity release (except where prohibited), which release will include the right to use the Weekly Challenge Winner&rsquo;s name and likeness in order to claim his/her prize, or such other documents as Sponsor deems necessary, in its sole discretion (collectively, &ldquo;Prize Claim Documents&rdquo;). If a Weekly Challenge Winner is a minor, a Prize either will be awarded in the name of the parent or legal guardian of such minor Weekly Challenge Winner.&nbsp; If a potential Weekly Challenge Winner cannot be contacted, fails to sign and return (or, in the case of a minor, such minor winner&rsquo;s parent or legal guardian fails to sign and return) the Prize Claim Documents within the required time period, potential Weekly Challenge Winner may be disqualified and may forfeit the prize. In the event that the potential Weekly Challenge Winner is disqualified for any reason, Sponsor may award the prize to the Entrant with the next highest number of points, time permitting.&nbsp; </p>
    <p><strong><u>Weekly Prizes</u></strong></p>
